üß© 1Ô∏è‚É£ What Are Data Types?
---------------------------------------------------
Data types tell Java what kind of value a variable can hold ‚Äî
whether it‚Äôs a number, text, true/false, or object.

Java has two main kinds:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Primitive Data Types ‚Üí Built-in types (fast, stored in stack)
2Ô∏è‚É£ Non-Primitive (Reference) Types ‚Üí Objects, arrays, strings, etc.


‚öôÔ∏è 2Ô∏è‚É£ Primitive Data Types
---------------------------------------------------
| Type     | Size    | Example                              | Description                        |
|-----------|---------|--------------------------------------|------------------------------------|
| byte      | 1 byte  | byte b = 100;                        | Small integers (-128 to 127)       |
| short     | 2 bytes | short s = 32000;                     | Medium-sized integers              |
| int       | 4 bytes | int age = 25;                        | Common integer type                |
| long      | 8 bytes | long population = 7800000000L;       | Large integers (note L)            |
| float     | 4 bytes | float price = 12.5f;                 | Decimal numbers (note f)           |
| double    | 8 bytes | double pi = 3.14159;                 | More precise decimal               |
| char      | 2 bytes | char grade = 'A';                    | Single character                   |
| boolean   | 1 bit   | boolean isActive = true;             | True or false                      |
*/